CI/CD optimization is crucial for accelerating software delivery and improving team productivity. This synthesis explores how caching strategies, particularly depot cache performance, can significantly enhance the efficiency of CI/CD pipelines. By understanding core concepts like build cache management and pipeline optimization techniques, teams can reduce build times and resource consumption. Key patterns include leveraging shared caches across pipelines and implementing smart cache invalidation policies. Advanced topics discuss trade-offs between cache granularity and network overhead.

